My Android apps of choice, many of which are cross-platform services.

## NoteTaking

* [Simplenote](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.automattic.simplenote) (text)
* [Squid](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.steadfastinnovation.android.projectpapyrus) (handwritten)
* [S-Note](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.samsung.android.snote) (quick memos)

## Weather

* [Weather Widget](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=se.stephanson.YRWidgetHD) - You have to see it to believe it. This is the first thing I put on a new phone.
* [Windy](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.windyty.android) - To be honest, I find the app is a little much for what I need, but it has great widgets.
* [Weawow](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.weawow) - Again, I don't personally use the app itself much, but nice widgets and you can set the widgets to report "feels like" temps (wind chill/humidex) which I prefer. (Why yes, I do have SIX different weather widgets spanning two of my home screens.)


## Twitter, News, RSS

* [Twitpane](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.twitpane) - I can't live with out this. How do you Twitter without this app?
* [Tweecha](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=net.sinproject.android.tweecha) - I love it *almost* as much as Twitpane. When I'm reading Blue Jays baseball Twitter on delay, this is the app I use to keep "current" in my "alternate timeline."  
* [Gravity](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=de.mobileways.gravity) (Yes, the old Nokia Twitter app on Android! Nostalgia!)
* [Slide for Reddit](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=me.ccrama.redditslide) - Don't forget to set up Synccit to sync between devices and with the website. ("Old Reddit" website only, though.)
* [Flym News Reader](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=net.frju.flym) - A simple, but elegant RSS feed reader. My fave to use, but does not synchronize with any online feed reader.
* [Feed Me RSS/Podcast](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.seazon.feedme) - The closest thing to Flym that syncs (I use Old Reader, but it works with several options.)

